'''Bara taboon''' (Arabek خبز طابون ''khubz tabun'') yw bara heb burm po bara leven an Levant pobys yn forn taboon po tandoor, hevelep dhe vara tandoori kevys yn lies rann a Asia. Usys yw avel goles po maylyans yn lies keginyeth, ha dybrys yw keveylyansow dyffrans ganso. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailyprincetonian.com/article/2002/02/falafel-ambassador-of-peace-or-cuisine-from-mideast |title=Falafel: Ambassador of peace or cuisine from mideast? |date=February 28, 2002 |last=Skloot |first=Joe |newspaper=The Daily Princetonian |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090819231855/http://www.dailyprincetonian.com/2002/02/28/4515/ |archive-date=2009-08-19 |url-status=unfit |access-date=2018-12-06}}</ref>

==Varyansow==
[[File:Tabun - 2.jpg|thumb|Taboon hengovek gans gorher dhyworth Palesteyn]]
Rann bosek a geginyeth palesteynek yw bara taboon, pobys yn hengovek war weli a veyn byghan pooth y'n forn ''taboon''. <ref name="Bethlehem U">{{cite web|access-date=2019-02-03|title=e-turathuna-Tabun - Bethlehem University|url=https://www.bethlehem.edu/3-ic/ic-lib/turathuna/topics/e-turathuna-tabun|website=www.bethlehem.edu}}</ref> Goles yw dhe ''musakhan'', prederys dhe vos boos kenedhlek Palesteyn.  Gustaf Dalman, studhyor almayenek a wonisogethow an Est, a skrifas ow tochya gul bara taboon yn Palesteyn y'n 20ves kansvledhen a-varr, yn mysk eghennow erel a vara. Yn Palesteyn, bara leven plegys a vedha lenwys yn fenowgh gans kemyskans a spinach hag onyon, po kemyskans a onyon ha kowles, po resin ha know saben. Bara taboon yw le yn aga myns dell yw usys ages bara ''tannur''. Dres an bledhynnyow pobas bara yn taboon kemmyn a waria rann gowethasek posek dhe venenes yn gwigow palesteynek. <ref name="Bethlehem U" />

Yn Israel, pobys yw bara leven meur-gerys aswonnys avel ''laffa'', hevel dhe bita yn Irak, po ashtanur yn Jerusalem ,<ref>[https://www.haaretz.com/food/.premium-eating-pious-pastries-in-mea-she-arim-1.5270497 Eating pious pastries in Mea She'arim], Haaretz</ref> yn ''tannur'' po ''taboon''.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Nadav |first1=Sarah |title=Let's meat at Aish: This off-the-beaten-track restaurant specializes in Eastern-style meats and delicious salads |url=http://www.jpost.com/Arts-and-Culture/Food-And-Wine/Lets-meat-at-Aish |access-date=2020-01-08 |work=The Jerusalem Post |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320111242/http://www.jpost.com/Arts-and-Culture/Food-And-Wine/Lets-meat-at-Aish |archive-date=2018-03-20 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishfederations.org/local_includes/downloads/21919.pdf |title=Did You Know? Israeli Cuisine |date=2010-09-04 |work=jewishfederations.org |publisher=Embassy of Israel, Washington, D.C. |access-date=2012-02-13 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106185432/http://www.jewishfederations.org/local_includes/downloads/21919.pdf |archive-date=2014-11-06 }}</ref> Kemmyn yw yn poptiow ha stallys boos yn le mayth yw usys dhe vaylya shawarma po boos aral.
